- 'Exceeded' means the average energy consumption was higher than the target energy consumption;
- '2020' refers to the year in the record time;
- 'monthly' target type indicates the target is set for each month.

- Target energy consumption refers to a predefined energy limit set for an appliance;
- Average energy consumption is the mean energy used by the appliance over a period;
- Total energy consumption is the sum of all energy used by the appliance;
- An active target status indicates that the target energy consumption is currently in effect.

- An appliance's target energy consumption is a predefined value that the appliance should not exceed.;
- An alert is triggered when an appliance's energy consumption exceeds its target energy consumption.;
- The percentage of target energy consumption is calculated as (average energy consumption / target energy consumption) * 100%.

- "Leading energy consumers" refers to appliances with the highest total energy consumption in each location;
- "Stars of a grand energy consumption spectacle" is a metaphor for the appliances that have the most significant impact on energy consumption;
- "Active energy consumption targets" indicate that the appliances are currently part of an ongoing energy management plan.

